Date: Thu 11 Jan 2001
From: Jack Woodall <woodall@promedmail.org>

Buried in the ProMED-mail post "Hepatitis - Russia & Belarus: update, 18
Dec 2000" was the following report:
"SARATOV (24 Nov 2000): According to the Saratov Oblast (province) Sanitary
& Epidemiological Service, the Oblast is at the end of epidemics of
hepatitis and hemorrhagic fever. By comparison with November 1999 the
number of hemorrhagic fever cases has increased 32-fold."
On Fri, 29 Dec 2000 Alex Vladyko <alex@promedmail.org>, ProMED-mail
Regional Moderator for the NIS/CIS, wrote:
"As I was able to [confirm, these were HFRS cases [hemorrhagic fever with
renal syndrome. Up to this moment there [are already nearly 2000 cases
with HFRS, 6 [of them fatal."
--
